Additional Services 





As a team-based medical home, we provide additional services to make sure that you and your family receive comprehensive and well-coordinated care. 

Women, Infants, and Children (WIC) program which provides supplemental foods, health care referrals, and nutrition education for low-income pregnant women and mothers with newborns, and for infants and children up to age five who are found to be at nutritional risk.

Health insurance enrollment counselors are available to help you enroll under the New York State of Health or government benefits, including Medicaid, Child Health Plus & Qualified Health Plan.  For more information, call 212-226-8339 (Manhattan) or 718- 886-7355 (Queens).  

Optometry services which includes general eye care examination, diagnosis, treatment and management of diseases and disorders that affect your vision.  By appointment only. 

Nutrition counseling by certified dieticians. By appointment only.

Language access line  at all sites to help translate for patients who speak languages that our staff does not speak. 

Patient portal will give you online access to easily communicate with your provider, refill your medication, request appointments, request referrals, request test results, send a message to your provider and view your medical summary.



   





